text:
Honestly unable to think of a single example on infinity that exists outside of math, even death ones own death is not infinite, since at least to me seems possible that the universe will die too, leaving nothing, which is the opposite of infinity to me. Maybe the universe is infinite, but we’re unable to my knowledge to reason out a way to prove it is.

Remember to Forget About Your Long Term Goals Every Day
text:
One of the problems of having a long term goal and strategy is that it becomes overwhelming when you think and plan too much.

For example, for my startup Proxies API one of the long-term goals is to write 100 articles in the year.

All this overwhelm means that when I wake up, I find it difficult to “get down to” the daily tasks that lead me to my goal in the first place. It is like my brain. Once it starts to think about long term goals and strategies, it can’t switch to doing simple tasks and tactics.

So every day, I wake up and revise my goals and strategies and get them out of the way. Once my brain is reassured that I am on the right track, I try to forget them altogether. Just try shaking it off with the promise of returning to it in the evening. Till then, no re-strategizing, no making sure we are on the right track. I am not even going to remember them.

It might be pronounced by some of you and is probably weird that I need to do it to myself, but hey, that’s how my brain is designed, and it’s a big deal for me now that I have discovered this works for me.

The author is the founder of Proxies API (https://www.proxiesapi.com/), a proxy rotation api service.

This article originally appeared here: https://www.proxiesapi.com/blog/Remember-To-Forget-About-Your-Long-Term-Goals-Every-Day.php

Mystery of Twitter Censorship
text:
When users share our company's product link https://dixel.club/, it shows "This Tweet is Unavailable." for other users in the thread. Demo: https://twitter.com/0xsebayaki/status/1569894288032677889. Try to check the main tweet on this thread.

I've read the guidelines in https://help.twitter.com/en/rules-and-policies/notices-on-twitter multiple times, but it doesn't explain a specific reason for "This Tweet is Unavailable". We've sent several appeals, but we are not getting any reply. It's nearly impossible to get any feedback from their support line. Can't they at least tell us the reason so we can fix the issue?

Our product is a NFT collection minting tool and a lot of our users share their collection link on Twitter, and this is really hurting our traction. We've spent months building our product, and we feel desperate considering that NFT related marketing is heavily focused on Twitter.

Could anyone provide pointers to fixing the issue? Please help us, we are lost and could use any help.

Show HN: A couple of links about Stable Diffusion AI Generation
text:
I've been studying Stable diffusion for some days and this Github page I linked in the title shows the incredible power that Stable Diffusion has Right now, and it is growing everyday. I think people on HN ought to know and discuss about it, and share their ideas and discoveries.

It can do text-to-image out of nothing with a customer-grade GPU, and image-to-image for incredible variations that you can guide with the criteria you choose.

https://imgur.com/a/Jt76AHA

Just check that picture out, I made variations from the base picture top-left, either to black-ened, or to white-ened, or to the combination of both... The power is infinite. It is called "Prompts matrix".

You can run it from your own computer preferably with 8GB VRAM+ GPU, or cloud-based virtual machine (I managed to run it on Microsoft Azure but not for cheap). To install Stable Diffusion and experiment for yourself, simply follow this page guidance: https://rentry.org/voldy#-guide-

If you just want to try out simply you can check out "beta.dreamstudio.ai" but it's not free beyond the first 200 images. It is free on Huggingface but it's struggling with the demand so I Won't link it.

It generates 512x512 imges, but you can ENHANCE the fuck out of it with this link: https://github.com/xinntao/Real-ESRGAN Check out the link "Portable Windows". You can commandline it and batch a whole folder with a .bat script, on Windows (and Unix of course). It's free, no strings attached (as far as I know).

If you generate texture or paintings you can generate a normal map and a displacement map, with CrazyBump.com. You can BATCH it a whole folder to their respective normals. There is a free trial which does the job, but buy it if you can, because it's awesome.

Here is a cool link about SD: https://lexica.art/ ("the SD search engine") Here's to showcase the most important PROMPTs the engine can handle: http://stable-diffusion-guide.s3-website-us-west-2.amazonaws... At this link, you can buy and sell PROMPTS: https://promptbase.com/ (it's a great place to have great ideas) Finally here's a database of prompts and their generated picture, to get ideas: https://laion-aesthetic.datasette.io/laion-aesthetic-6pls/im...

That's it for what I learned as of know. I hope people will talk about that and so we can get more nerds into the Stable Diffusion and make it even more open and awesome.

Thank you for reading
